.TH WT 1 "March 2026" "wt" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
wt \- convenient Git worktree manager

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wt
.I command
[args]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wt
is a tiny bash wrapper that makes Git worktrees delightful.
It automatically cds, prevents nesting, and adds sensible defaults.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B add <name>
Create a new branch + worktree and switch into it.

.TP
.B co <name>
Switch to an existing worktree or add one for an existing branch (local or remote).

.TP
.B rm [-f] [<name>]
Remove the current worktree (no argument) or a specific one.
The \-f / \-\-force flag forces removal even if the worktree is dirty.

.TP
.B prune
Run git worktree prune (removes stale entries).

.TP
.B ls
List all worktrees (git worktree list).

.TP
.B mv <old> <new>
Move a worktree and rename the branch inside it.

.TP
.B help
Show usage.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I <repo>/.worktree/<name>
All worktrees are stored here (add to .gitignore).

.SH AUTHOR
Maurice

.SH SEE ALSO
git-worktree(1)
